/**
 * Site and Point service using Cloudflare Worker
 * All ACE IoT API calls go through the edge-based Worker with built-in caching
 */
import { cloudflareWorkerClient } from '../api/cloudflareWorkerClient';
import type { Site, Point } from '../../types/api';
import store from '../../store';
import { enhancePointWithKvTags, hasKvTags } from '../../utils/kvTagParser';

class CachedSitePointService {
  private static instance: CachedSitePointService;

  private constructor() {
    // Nothing to initialize - aceIotApiClient handles everything
  }

  public static getInstance(): CachedSitePointService {
    if (!CachedSitePointService.instance) {
      CachedSitePointService.instance = new CachedSitePointService();
    }
    return CachedSitePointService.instance;
  }

  /**
   * Fetch all sites - uses Cloudflare Worker
   */
  public async fetchSites(): Promise<Site[]> {
    try {
      // Set token if available
      const aceToken = store.getState().auth.aceToken;
      if (aceToken) {
        cloudflareWorkerClient.setToken(aceToken);
      }
      
      // Fetch sites from Cloudflare Worker
      const response = await cloudflareWorkerClient.fetchSites();
      console.log('[CachedSitePointService] Response from cloudflareWorkerClient:', response);
      
      // cloudflareWorkerClient now normalizes all responses to have 'items' field
      const sites = response?.items || [];
      
      console.log(`[CachedSitePointService] Found ${sites.length} sites`);
      return sites;
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('[CachedSitePointService] Failed to fetch sites:', error);
      // Re-throw the error for proper error handling in UI
      throw error;
    }
  }

  /**
   * Fetch points for a specific site - uses Cloudflare Worker
   * By default, fetches only collect-enabled points for chart selection
   */
  public async fetchPointsForSite(
    siteId: string,
    _aceToken?: string,
    _onProgress?: (loaded: number, total: number) => void,
    collectEnabledOnly: boolean = true,
    bypassCache: boolean = false
  ): Promise<{ all: Point[]; grouped: Record<string, Point[]> }> {
    try {
      // Set token if available
      const aceToken = _aceToken || store.getState().auth.aceToken;
      if (aceToken) {
        cloudflareWorkerClient.setToken(aceToken);
      }

      console.log(
        '[CachedSitePointService] fetchPointsForSite called with siteId:',
        siteId,
        'type:',
        typeof siteId
      );

      // CRITICAL FIX: Convert numeric site ID to site name
      // The Cloudflare Worker expects site names (like "ses_falls_city") not numeric IDs (like "309")
      let siteIdentifier = siteId;

      // Check if it's a numeric ID
      if (!isNaN(parseInt(siteId, 10))) {
        console.log('[CachedSitePointService] Numeric site ID detected, need to convert:', siteId);

        // Fetch sites to find the correct name
        const sitesResponse = await cloudflareWorkerClient.fetchSites();
        const sites = sitesResponse?.items || [];

        // Find the site by numeric ID
        const site = sites.find(s =>
          s.id === siteId ||
          s.id === parseInt(siteId, 10) ||
          s.id?.toString() === siteId ||
          parseInt(s.id as string, 10) === parseInt(siteId, 10)
        );

        if (site && site.name) {
          console.log('[CachedSitePointService] Found site name:', site.name, 'for ID:', siteId);
          siteIdentifier = site.name;
        } else {
          console.warn('[CachedSitePointService] Could not find site name for ID:', siteId);
          // Fallback: try using the ID anyway, maybe it's already a name
        }
      }

      console.log('[CachedSitePointService] Using site identifier for API:', siteIdentifier);

      // Fetch points from Cloudflare Worker using site name
      const response = await cloudflareWorkerClient.fetchPoints(siteIdentifier, bypassCache);
      // cloudflareWorkerClient now normalizes all responses to have 'items' field
      let points: Point[] = response?.items || [];

      // Log the response details
      console.log('[CachedSitePointService] Points response:', {
        totalPoints: points.length,
        fromCache: response?.fromCache,
        message: response?.message,
        aiEnhanced: response?.aiEnhanced
      });

      // Map Worker's display_name to displayName and enhance points with KV tags
      console.log('[CachedSitePointService] Enhancing points with KV tags...');
      points = points.map(point => {
        // Map worker's snake_case display_name to camelCase displayName
        const mappedPoint = {
          ...point,
          displayName: (point as any).display_name || point.displayName || point.name
        };

        // Check if point has KV tags to parse
        if (hasKvTags(mappedPoint)) {
          const enhanced = enhancePointWithKvTags(mappedPoint);
          console.log('[CachedSitePointService] Enhanced point:', {
            original: enhanced.name,
            displayName: enhanced.displayName,
            equipment: enhanced.equipment,
            unit: enhanced.unit
          });
          return enhanced;
        }
        return mappedPoint;
      });

      if (collectEnabledOnly) {
        // Filter to only collect-enabled points client-side
        const filtered = points.filter((p) => (p as any).collect_enabled !== false);
        console.log(
          `[CachedSitePointService] Filtered ${points.length} points to ${filtered.length} collect-enabled points`
        );
        points = filtered;
      }

      // Group points by category for backward compatibility
      const grouped = this.groupPointsByCategory(points);

      return {
        all: points,
        grouped,
      };
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('[CachedSitePointService] Failed to fetch points:', error);
      throw error;
    }
  }

  /**
   * Search points - uses Cloudflare Worker
   */
  public async searchPoints(searchPattern: string, siteId?: string): Promise<Point[]> {
    try {
      const aceToken = store.getState().auth.aceToken;
      if (aceToken) {
        cloudflareWorkerClient.setToken(aceToken);
      }
      
      // If siteId is provided, fetch points for that site and filter
      if (siteId) {
        const response = await cloudflareWorkerClient.fetchPoints(siteId);
        const points = response?.items || [];
        // Filter points by search pattern
        return points.filter(point => 
          point.name.toLowerCase().includes(searchPattern.toLowerCase()) ||
          point.description?.toLowerCase().includes(searchPattern.toLowerCase())
        );
      } else {
        // Without siteId, we need to fetch all sites and their points
        // This is inefficient but maintains backward compatibility
        const sitesResponse = await cloudflareWorkerClient.fetchSites();
        const sites = sitesResponse?.items || [];
        const allPoints: Point[] = [];
        
        for (const site of sites) {
          try {
            const response = await cloudflareWorkerClient.fetchPoints(site.id);
            const points = response?.items || [];
            allPoints.push(...points);
          } catch (err) {
            console.warn(`Failed to fetch points for site ${site.id}:`, err);
          }
        }
        
        // Filter all points by search pattern
        return allPoints.filter(point => 
          point.name.toLowerCase().includes(searchPattern.toLowerCase()) ||
          point.description?.toLowerCase().includes(searchPattern.toLowerCase())
        );
      }
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('[CachedSitePointService] Failed to search points:', error);
      // Re-throw the error for proper error handling in UI
      throw error;
    }
  }

  /**
   * Group points by category - kept for backward compatibility
   */
  private groupPointsByCategory(points: Point[]): Record<string, Point[]> {
    const grouped: Record<string, Point[]> = {};

    points.forEach((point) => {
      const category = point.point_type || 'Other';
      if (!grouped[category]) {
        grouped[category] = [];
      }
      grouped[category].push(point);
    });

    return grouped;
  }

  /**
   * Get ACE token from Redux store
   */
  private async getAceToken(): Promise<string> {
    const aceToken = store.getState().auth.aceToken;
    if (!aceToken) {
      throw new Error('No ACE IoT token found. Please add your token in Settings.');
    }
    return aceToken;
  }

  /**
   * Compatibility method - no longer needed
   */
  public async initialize(): Promise<void> {
    // Nothing to initialize
  }

  /**
   * Compatibility method - no longer needed
   */
  public clearCache(): void {
    // Caching is handled by Firebase Functions
  }

  /**
   * Prefetch common data - uses Cloudflare Worker
   * This method is for backward compatibility
   */
  public async prefetchCommonData(): Promise<void> {
    try {
      const aceToken = store.getState().auth.aceToken;
      if (!aceToken) {
        // Skip prefetch if no token
        return;
      }

      // Set token and prefetch sites to warm up the cache
      cloudflareWorkerClient.setToken(aceToken);
      await cloudflareWorkerClient.fetchSites();
    } catch (error) {
      // Ignore prefetch errors
      console.debug('Prefetch error (non-critical):', error);
    }
  }
}

// Export singleton instance
export const cachedSitePointService = CachedSitePointService.getInstance();

// Export the class itself for backward compatibility
export { CachedSitePointService };
